Combined net income of 62 brokerages
in April-June fell to 216.3b won from yr earlier, Financial
Supervisory Service says in e-mailed statement.
*Brokerage fees dropped 37% as equity trading value declined
amid continued uncertainty in financial markets: FSS 
*62 firms include 42 domestic brokerages and 11 branches of
foreign companies: FSS
*NOTE: Benchmark Kospi index slipped 7.95% in April-June  To contact the reporter on this story:
